===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|comly}}, {{m|enm|cumly}}, {{m|enm|cumlich}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|cymlīc}}, {{term|lang=ang|cȳmlīċ}} (compare Old English {{term|lang=ang|cȳme||fine, exquisite}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|ang}} {{m|gem-pro|*kūmiz||delicate}}), from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*kūmalīkaz||pitiful, dear}}. Cognate with Middle Dutch {{m|dum|komlick}}, {{m|dum|komelick}}, Middle High German {{m|gmh|komelīh}}, {{m|gmh|gomelīh}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈkʌmli/|lang=en}}
